Label: Administrative Region Level 0
Description: GADM level 0 administrative regions which represent countries.

Label: Administrative Region Level 1
Description: GADM level 1 administrative regions which are the highest level of division of a country, such as US states, Canadian provinces, or French departments.

Label: Administrative Region Level 2
Description: GADM level 2 administrative regions which further subdivide states, provinces, or departments. Examples include counties in the US

Label: Administrative Region
Description: Administrative regoins as defined by the Global Administrative Area Database (GADM); see https://gadm.org/metadata.html

Label: S2 Cell Level 13
Description: S2 geometric cell at level 13 resolution

Label: Spatial Object
Description: Object with spatial location or extent

Label: Active Ingredient
Description: Active chemical ingredient in pesticides or amendments

Label: Amendment
Description: Soil or crop amendment applied in agricultural experiments

Label: Amendment Placement
Description: Method or location of amendment application

Label: Amendment Type
Description: Classification of amendment types used in agriculture

Label: Animal Class
Description: Classification of animals used in grazing experiments

Label: Animal Species
Description: Specific species of animals used in agricultural studies

Label: Biomass Analysis
Description: Analysis and measurement of plant biomass

Label: Broadleaf or Grass
Description: Classification indicating whether a plant is broadleaf or grass

Label: Chamber Placement
Description: Location or setup of measurement chambers

Label: Cover Crop
Description: Crops planted to cover soil rather than for harvest

Label: Crop Related Measurement
Description: Measurements related to crop growth and development

Label: Cultivar
Description: Specific variety of a cultivated plant

Label: Cutting Height
Description: Height at which crops are cut or harvested

Label: Equipment
Description: Agricultural equipment used in experiments or farming

Label: Experimental Unit
Description: Basic unit of experimentation in agricultural studies

Label: Funding Source
Description: Organization or entity providing research funding

Label: Gas Nutrient Loss
Description: Loss of nutrients through gaseous emissions

Label: GHG Flux
Description: Measurement of greenhouse gas flux from soil

Label: Grazing Rate
Description: Rate at which animals graze vegetation

Label: Growth Stage Management
Description: Management practices at specific growth stages

Label: Growth Stage Related Measurement
Description: Measurements taken at specific growth stages

Label: Harvested Fraction
Description: Portion of crop that is harvested

Label: Harvest Fraction
Description: Fraction of biomass removed during harvest

Label: Location
Description: Geographic location of experimental site or field

Label: Measurable Entity
Description: Entity that can be measured or quantified

Label: Nutrient Efficiency
Description: Efficiency of nutrient use by crops

Label: Parameter
Description: Variable or factor in agricultural experiments

Label: Pesticide Placement
Description: Method or location of pesticide application

Label: Pesticide Target
Description: Pest or disease targeted by pesticide

Label: Plant Fraction
Description: Specific part or fraction of a plant

Label: Popular Article
Description: Article in popular or non-peer-reviewed publication

Label: Possibly Simulated Measurement
Description: Measurement that may be simulated rather than observed

Label: Project Scenario
Description: Specific scenario within a research project

Label: Residue Management
Description: Management of crop residues after harvest

Label: Residue Measurement
Description: Measurement of crop residue quantity or quality

Label: Residue Removal
Description: Removal of crop residues from field

Label: Rotation
Description: Sequence of crops planted in succession

Label: Site
Description: Physical location where experiments are conducted

Label: Soil Biological Sample
Description: Soil sample analyzed for biological properties

Label: Soil Chemical Sample
Description: Soil sample analyzed for chemical properties

Label: Soil Cover
Description: Material or vegetation covering soil surface

Label: Soil Physical Sample
Description: Soil sample analyzed for physical properties

Label: Soil Sample
Description: Sample of soil collected for analysis

Label: Start Stop Interval
Description: Time interval with defined start and stop points

Label: Surface or Leaching
Description: Process occurring at surface or through leaching

Label: Timing
Description: Temporal aspect or schedule of activities

Label: Treatment
Description: Experimental treatment applied to crops or soil

Label: Water Quality Area
Description: Spatial extent related to water quality

Label: Yield Nutrient Uptake
Description: Nutrient uptake related to crop yield

Label: Soil organic carbon
Description: Class representing soil organic carbon in the knowledge graph

Label: creator
Description: Entity responsible for creating the resource

Label: date
Description: Date associated with an event in the lifecycle of the resource

Label: is Part Of
Description: Related resource in which the described resource is physically or logically included

Label: issued
Description: Date of formal issuance of the resource

Label: topological connection (spatial contact) (sawgraph)
Description: Indicates topological connection or spatial contact between entities

Label: has Unit
Description: Links a quantity value to its unit of measurement

Label: quantity Value
Description: Relates an entity to its quantity value

Label: standard Uncertainty
Description: Standard uncertainty associated with a measurement

Label: sfContains (kwg)
Description: Spatial relationship indicating one geometry contains another

Label: sfWithin (kwg)
Description: Spatial relationship indicating one geometry is within another

Label: has Geometry
Description: Links a feature to its geometric representation

Label: disjoint With
Description: Indicates classes that have no common instances

Label: bad Value Flag
Description: Flag indicating potentially erroneous data value

Label: end Date
Description: End date of time period or event

Label: from Project
Description: Links data to originating research project

Label: has Broadleaf or Grass
Description: Classification as broadleaf or grass plant

Label: has Chamber Placement
Description: Location or setup of measurement chamber

Label: has Losses or Deposition
Description: Type of nutrient loss or deposition

Label: has Surface or Leaching
Description: Type of surface or leaching process

Label: inferred
Description: Indicates value was inferred rather than measured

Label: lower Depth
Description: Lower boundary depth of soil sample

Label: of
Description: Generic relationship indicating belonging or association

Label: start Date
Description: Start date of time period or event

Label: unit Has Growth Stage Management
Description: Growth stage management in experimental unit

Label: upper Depth
Description: Upper boundary depth of soil sample

Label: with Cutting Height
Description: Height at which crop is cut
